rooms.long_description:
You are standing in a rocky windswept desert. Huge black outcroppings of
rock block travel in all directions except to the east and southwest. The
entrance to a crude circular stone building lies to the north.

room_flags.note: Bitwise OR of flag values from _enumerations.room_flags

rooms.long_description:
You are standing in a stonework chamber, fitted with dull grey stone tiles.
The room is rectangular in shape and is roughly thirty feet by fifty feet
across. The western wall bears this cryptic message: "Speak the element of
the guardian of the temple catacombs in the language of spellcraft to gain
entrance." The visible exits are south and east through stone archways
fitted with massive iron doors. There is also a stone archway leading out
into the desert to the north.
